.name
Popper
.description
Replaces Intuition menus with popup menus which appear under
the mouse pointer instead of in the top of the screen.  You
can also "rip" menus from the menu-bar and keep them on the
screen as a window all the time (or close them with the close
gadget, of course). 
.short
Popup menus
.type
WorkBench Tool
.version
1.1
.exectype
binary only.
.author
Pierre Dak Baillargeon
.described-by
David Zaroski (cz253@cleveland.freenet.edu)
